# RAG UI Architecture

## State Management: Zustand (single store)

- All state lives in `src/store/useStore.ts`
- Components access state via `const { ... } = useStore()`
- No prop drilling — any component can read/write any state
- Actions are defined alongside state in the store

## Service Layer

Two service files hold ALL business logic, separate from UI:

- `src/services/documentParser.ts` — PDF/DOCX/TXT text extraction
- `src/services/textAnalyzer.ts` — Unreadable detection, terminology, conflict detection, FAQ generation, guideline validation, DOCX export

When adding new analysis features, add them to `textAnalyzer.ts` and wire into `runIngestion()` in the store.

## Component Structure

Each workflow step = one component file in `src/components/`:

| Step | Component | CSS |
|------|-----------|-----|
| 0 | Upload.tsx | Upload.css |
| 1 | UnreadableContentStep.tsx | Steps.css |
| 2 | TerminologyStep.tsx | Steps.css |
| 3 | ConflictStep.tsx | Steps.css |
| 4 | FAQStep.tsx | Steps.css |
| 5 | FinalReviewStep.tsx | Steps.css |

`App.tsx` is a simple step-router. `Layout.tsx` renders the sidebar + navigation.

## Adding a New Step

1. Create `src/components/NewStep.tsx`
2. Add step to the `steps` array in `Layout.tsx`
3. Add `{currentStep === N && <NewStep />}` in `App.tsx`
4. Add any new state to `useStore.ts`
5. Update test mocks in `src/tests/flow.test.tsx`

## Key Conventions

- Functional components only (no class components)
- Framer Motion for animations (`motion.div`, `AnimatePresence`)
- Lucide React for all icons
- Step footers MUST use `sticky-foot` class
- Every processing step MUST have a "Skip for Now" button
